This paper deals with the problem of reconstructing the dependency structure of a Markov random field from independent samples, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The paper presents an algorithmic approach to this problem and analyzes its performance under certain conditions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
